gomodel:SYNGO_3750  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Figures 3A,B,D,E: postsynaptic spines were also clearly labeled, with immunogold labeling showing a somewhat similar labeling pattern as in the presynaptic terminal. Gold particles were noticably associated with the PSD (Figures 3D,F), but many postsynaptic vesicles were also immunopositive (Figures 3A,B). Some gold particles were also located along the pre- and postsynaptic lateral membranes. In dendrites, gold particles were associated with cytoplasmic vesicles along microtubules and attached to the DM (Figure 3C).\nFigure 5 shows quantification of immune-gold particles at postsynapse.\nFigure 6 shows postsynaptic colocalization with NMDA and AMPA receptors.\n\n19/6/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: M&M: Electron micrographs from RATS (n = 3) were obtained from asymmetric synapses (Schaffer collateral synapses) from the middle layer of stratum radiatum of the CA1 region of the hippocampus." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" ;
